.TH "mark_inode_clean" 9 "mark_inode_clean" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
mark_inode_clean \- mark UBIFS inode as clean.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" mark_inode_clean
.BI "(struct ubifs_info *c "  ","
.BI "struct ubifs_inode *ui "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "c" 12
UBIFS file-system description object
.IP "ui" 12
UBIFS inode to mark as clean
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This helper function marks UBIFS inode \fIui\fP as clean by cleaning the
\fIui->dirty\fP flag and releasing its budget. Note, VFS may still treat the
inode as dirty and try to write it back, but '\fBubifs_write_inode\fP' would
just do nothing.
